   MealEase Planner Logic

   Purpose

The logic for the MealEase Planner application allows the user to enter meals for each day of the week, create a grocery list, enter a grocery budget, and determine whether the total grocery cost is within the selected budget.

---

  Main Meal Planner Pseudocode

```text
Start

    Display "Welcome to MealEase Planner"

    Call getUserInformation()
    Call enterWeeklyBudget()
    Call createWeeklyMealPlan()
    Call createGroceryList()
    Call calculateGroceryTotal()
    Call compareBudget()
    Call displayMealPlan()

Stop
```

---

  User Information Module

```text
Module getUserInformation()

    Declare String userName
    Declare Integer familySize

    Display "Enter your name:"
    Input userName

    Display "Enter the number of people in your family:"
    Input familySize

    Display "Welcome, ", userName
    Display "You are planning meals for ", familySize, " people."

End Module
```

---

  Weekly Budget Module

```text
Module enterWeeklyBudget()

    Declare Real weeklyBudget

    Display "Enter your weekly grocery budget:"
    Input weeklyBudget

    While weeklyBudget <= 0
        Display "Please enter a budget greater than zero:"
        Input weeklyBudget
    End While

End Module
```

---

  Weekly Meal Plan Module

```text
Module createWeeklyMealPlan()

    Declare Integer day
    Declare String breakfast[7]
    Declare String lunch[7]
    Declare String dinner[7]
    Declare String snack[7]

    For day = 0 To 6

        Display "Enter breakfast for ", getDayName(day), ":"
        Input breakfast[day]

        Display "Enter lunch for ", getDayName(day), ":"
        Input lunch[day]

        Display "Enter dinner for ", getDayName(day), ":"
        Input dinner[day]

        Display "Enter a snack for ", getDayName(day), ":"
        Input snack[day]

    End For

End Module
```

---

  Day Name Function

```text
Function String getDayName(Integer day)

    Declare String days[7] = "Monday", "Tuesday", "Wednesday",
                             "Thursday", "Friday", "Saturday",
                             "Sunday"

    Return days[day]

End Function
```

---

  Grocery List Module

```text
Module createGroceryList()

    Declare Integer numberOfItems
    Declare Integer index
    Declare String groceryItem[]
    Declare Real itemPrice[]

    Display "How many grocery items do you need?"
    Input numberOfItems

    For index = 0 To numberOfItems - 1

        Display "Enter grocery item ", index + 1, ":"
        Input groceryItem[index]

        Display "Enter the estimated price of ", groceryItem[index], ":"
        Input itemPrice[index]

    End For

End Module
```

---

  Calculate Grocery Total Function

```text
Function Real calculateGroceryTotal()

    Declare Integer index
    Declare Real groceryTotal = 0

    For index = 0 To numberOfItems - 1
        Set groceryTotal = groceryTotal + itemPrice[index]
    End For

    Return groceryTotal

End Function
```

---

  Compare Budget Module

```text
Module compareBudget()

    Declare Real remainingMoney

    Set remainingMoney = weeklyBudget - groceryTotal

    If groceryTotal <= weeklyBudget Then

        Display "Your meal plan is within your grocery budget."
        Display "Your estimated grocery total is $", groceryTotal
        Display "You have $", remainingMoney, " remaining."

    Else

        Set remainingMoney = groceryTotal - weeklyBudget

        Display "Your meal plan is over your grocery budget."
        Display "Your estimated grocery total is $", groceryTotal
        Display "You are $", remainingMoney, " over budget."

    End If

End Module
```

---

  Display Weekly Meal Plan Module

```text
Module displayMealPlan()

    Declare Integer day

    Display "MealEase Weekly Meal Plan"
    Display "--------------------------"

    For day = 0 To 6

        Display getDayName(day)

        Display "Breakfast: ", breakfast[day]
        Display "Lunch: ", lunch[day]
        Display "Dinner: ", dinner[day]
        Display "Snack: ", snack[day]

        Display "--------------------------"

    End For

End Module
```

---

  Grocery List Display Module

```text
Module displayGroceryList()

    Declare Integer index

    Display "Grocery Shopping List"
    Display "---------------------"

    For index = 0 To numberOfItems - 1

        Display groceryItem[index], " - $", itemPrice[index]

    End For

    Display "Estimated Total: $", groceryTotal

End Module
```

